## Task
> Fix the broken nx storybook dev-server in this Nx Angular library: `nx storybook ngx-smart-components` fails with `SB_FRAMEWORK_ANGULAR_0001 AngularLegacyBuildOptionsError` ('You must use Angular builder to have an explicit configuration on the project used in angular.json. Please run npx storybook automigrate') while `nx build-storybook` succeeds.

## Orientation Findings

1. The library is a single Angular library package (`packages/ngx-smart-components`). Framework: `@storybook/angular@10.3.5`, Nx 22.6.5, Angular 21.2.x. The workspace has no `angular.json` (Nx standalone workspace using `project.json` only).

2. `storybook` executor in `project.json` uses `@storybook/angular:start-storybook` (direct Storybook Angular builder). `build-storybook` uses `@storybook/angular:build-storybook`. Neither currently has a `browserTarget` in options. Both have `compodoc: true` and `compodocArgs` pointing to `tsconfig.lib.json`.

3. `build-storybook` works because its schema (`build-schema.json`) defines `"default": null` for `browserTarget`. When omitted from `project.json`, the Angular DevKit schema validation yields `options.browserTarget = null`. `start-storybook`'s schema (`start-schema.json`) has NO default for `browserTarget` -- when omitted, `options.browserTarget = undefined`.

4. The `checkForLegacyBuildOptions` function in `framework-preset-angular-cli.js` (line 157-160) only throws when `options.angularBrowserTarget === undefined` (strict equality with `void 0`), NOT when `null`:
   ```javascript
   function checkForLegacyBuildOptions(options) {
     if (options.angularBrowserTarget === void 0)
       throw new AngularLegacyBuildOptionsError();
   }
   ```
   `angularBrowserTarget` comes directly from `options.browserTarget` in the builder: `angularBrowserTarget: browserTarget` where `browserTarget` is destructured from `options`. So undefined → throws; null → passes.

5. Regression introduced in commit `a1f53ee` ("fix(ngx-smart-components): address Storybook Compodoc review findings"): removed `"browserTarget": "ngx-smart-components:build-storybook"` from both the `storybook` AND `build-storybook` executor options, with incorrect justification that "@storybook/angular 10.3.5 schema defines default: null so omitting is correct". The `build-schema.json` DOES have `default: null` but `start-schema.json` does NOT.

6. Prior to commit `a1f53ee` (commit `87a982a`), both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets had `"browserTarget": "ngx-smart-components:build-storybook"`. The dev server worked with this self-referential target string.

7. The `getBuilderOptions` function uses `if (options.angularBrowserTarget)` (falsy check) not strict equality -- so when `angularBrowserTarget` is null (from `build-storybook`), it skips `getTargetOptions` lookup and falls back to `up("tsconfig.json", ...)` which walks up from `.storybook/` and finds `packages/ngx-smart-components/tsconfig.json`.

8. `@angular-devkit/build-angular` IS installed (confirmed by file existence check). This means the early-return guard in `webpackFinal` (`if (!resolvePackageDir("@angular-devkit/build-angular")) return`) does NOT skip the `checkForLegacyBuildOptions` call.

9. `@nx/storybook:storybook` executor is a thin wrapper around `storybook/internal/core-server::build()` and does NOT inject `browserTarget` automatically. Switching to it would not help.

## Pre-Verified Package Behavior Claims

<pre_verified source="node_modules/@storybook/angular/start-schema.json" claim_id="pv-start-schema-no-default">
  <claim>@storybook/angular@10.3.5 start-schema.json has no `default` property for `browserTarget` -- the field is optional with type string and a pattern but no default value.</claim>
  <evidence method="Read">
    "browserTarget": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Build target to be served in project-name:builder:config format. Should generally target on the builder: '@angular-devkit/build-angular:browser'. Useful for Storybook to use options (styles, assets, ...).",
      "pattern": "^[^:\\s]+:[^:\\s]+(:[^\\s]+)?$"
    },
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

<pre_verified source="node_modules/@storybook/angular/build-schema.json" claim_id="pv-build-schema-null-default">
  <claim>@storybook/angular@10.3.5 build-schema.json DOES have `"default": null` for `browserTarget`.</claim>
  <evidence method="Read">
    "browserTarget": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Build target to be served in project-name:builder:config format. Should generally target on the builder: '@angular-devkit/build-angular:browser'. Useful for Storybook to use options (styles, assets, ...).",
      "pattern": "^[^:\\s]+:[^:\\s]+(:[^\\s]+)?$",
      "default": null
    },
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

<pre_verified source="node_modules/@storybook/angular/dist/server/framework-preset-angular-cli.js" claim_id="pv-check-legacy-build-options">
  <claim>`checkForLegacyBuildOptions` throws `AngularLegacyBuildOptionsError` when `options.angularBrowserTarget === void 0` (strict undefined check), NOT when null.</claim>
  <evidence method="Read">
    function checkForLegacyBuildOptions(options) {
      if (options.angularBrowserTarget === void 0)
        throw new AngularLegacyBuildOptionsError();
    }
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

<pre_verified source="node_modules/@storybook/angular/dist/builders/start-storybook/index.js" claim_id="pv-start-builder-browser-target">
  <claim>In start-storybook, `angularBrowserTarget` is set to `options.browserTarget` (destructured directly from options), meaning undefined when not supplied via schema default.</claim>
  <evidence method="Read">
    let {
      browserTarget,
      ...
    } = options, ...
    standaloneOptions = {
      ...
      angularBrowserTarget: browserTarget,
      angularBuilderContext: context,
  </evidence>
</pre_verified>

## Relevant File Contents

`packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` storybook and build-storybook targets (current, post-a1f53ee):
```json
